                                    <locus from="1v" to="2v"/>
                                    <q xml:lang="gez"><seg part="I">ይትባረክ፡ ስሙ፡ ለእግዚአብሔር፡ ቡሩክ፡ ይትአኮት፡ እኩት፡ ይትቀደስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ይሴባሕ፡ ስሙ፡ ለእግዚአብሔር፡
                                        ስቡሕ፡ ይዕበይ፡ ስሙ፡ ለእግዚአብሔር፡ ዓቢይ፡ ይትለዓል፡ ስሙ፡ ለእግዚአብሔር፡ ልዑል፡</seg></q>
                                    <q xml:lang="gez"><seg part="F">ያግሕስክሙ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ለለአሐዱ፡ ትካዘ፡ ይናዝዝ፡ እ<hi rend="ligature">ግዚ</hi>አብሔር፡ ለለአሐዱ፡
                                        መፍቅዶ፡ ይሥራ፡ እ<hi rend="ligature">ግዚ</hi>አብሔር፡ ወለለአሐዱ፡ ዳዕሮ፡ ወስቃዮ፡ ያንኂ፡ እ<hi rend="ligature">ግዚ</hi>አብሔር፡</seg></q>
                                </item>

                                <item xml:id="e1">
                                    <desc>Many corrections are executed over erasure (e.g. on <locus target="#10ra #20va #38va"/>), sometimes in small script to accommodate multiple lines (e.g.
                                        <locus target="#23rb #31rb #40va"/>). Many corrections, executed either over erasure or interlineally, are written in the same hand as that of <ref target="#e3">the
                                            aids for identifying weekday readings</ref>. The spaces left after erasures are sometimes marked with thin lines (e.g. on <locus target="#11rb"/>).
                                        Erasures are also found in the upper margins in correspondence of the incipit of the weekday readings (e.g. on <locus target="#16vb #40vb #69rb"/>).
                                        The name of an individual, indicated as <foreign xml:lang="gez">ገብሩ፡</foreign> ‘his servant’ (probably either the owner, the patron or the donor of
                                        the manuscript), has been erased on <locus target="#3r"/>. Few words are washed out on <locus target="#46va #53vb #64vb"/>.
                                    </desc>
                                </item>
                                
                                <item xml:id="e2">
                                    <desc>Aids for identifying weekday readings are written in the upper margin within a frame, probably in the same hand as that of <ref target="#a1"/>:
                                        <q xml:lang="gez">ዘስኑይ</q> (<locus target="#3r"/>), <q xml:lang="gez"><sic>ዘቀዳም</sic></q> (<locus target="#16vb"/>),
                                        <q xml:lang="gez">ዘሠሉስ</q> (<locus target="#20vb"/>), <q xml:lang="gez">ዘረቡዕ</q> (<locus target="#40va"/>),
                                        <q xml:lang="gez">ዘሐሙስ</q> (<locus target="#48vb"/>), <q xml:lang="gez">ዘዓርብ</q> (<locus target="#61va"/>),
                                        <q xml:lang="gez">ዘእሁድ።</q> (<locus target="#69ra"/>).
                                    </desc>
                                </item>
                                
                                <item xml:id="e3">
                                    <desc>
                                        A <hi rendition="simple:italic">tamallas</hi>-sign in the shape of a cross indicates on <locus target="#49vb"/> the omission of a portion of text,
                                        which is written in the upper margin. Both the <hi rendition="simple:italic">tamallas</hi>-sign and the omitted text are written in the same hand as
                                        that of <ref target="#e2">the aids for the weekday readings</ref> and of many corrections.
                                    </desc>
                                </item>
                                
                                <item xml:id="e4">
                                    <desc>There are some writings in pencil on <locus target="#1r"/>: ‘Brought from
                                        <persName ref="PRS13027Sturt" role="owner"><roleName type="rank">Capt.</roleName> Sturt</persName> from
                                        <placeName ref="LOC3010Ethiop">Ethiopia</placeName>’ and
                                       ‘Gospel of John’. The titles of the manuscript contents are indicated in the same handwriting in pencil in the upper margin of
                                        <locus target="#3r"/> (‘Gospel of John’) and <locus target="#75v"/> (‘Hymns to the Virgin’).
                                    </desc>
                                </item>
                                
                                <item xml:id="e5">
                                    <desc>A white sticker is glued to the inner side of the front board. The name of <persName ref="PRS5782JuelJen"/> is printed on it
                                        (‘<foreign xml:lang="gez">ቤንት፡ ዩውል፡ የንሰን።</foreign>’) and the signature ‘MS. Aeth. f. 31’ is written in pencil.
                                        An additional sticker, with the signature ‘Ms 21’ on it, is glued below it.</desc>
                                </item>
                            </list>
